<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Multiple arbitrage</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A dollar of income is worth more in some busin=
esses than in others. Some businesses are attractive and fast-growing, and =
investors will pay a large multiple of their current earnings to buy them; =
other businesses are boring and declining, and investors will pay a small m=
ultiple of their current earnings to buy them. Nvidia Corp.=E2=80=99s stock=
 trades at about 36 times earnings=C2=A0because people want to own a busine=
ss that sells graphics chips in an artificial intelligence boom; Peabody En=
ergy trades at about 6 times earnings=C2=A0because people are less jazzed a=
bout owning a coal miner in 2024.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footn=
ote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bo=
ttom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !i=
mportant; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;"=
>
<span>[1]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Many companies have multiple lines of business=
. You can do a sum-of-the-parts valuation on those companies, looking at th=
e earnings of each segment and applying some reasonable market multiple to =
those earnings. If for some reason you had a conglomerate that made $1 bill=
ion selling graphics chips and $1 billion selling thermal coal, you might e=
stimate that the graphics-chip division was worth about $36 billion (using =
Nvidia=E2=80=99s multiple) and the coal division was worth about $6 billion=
 (using Peabody=E2=80=99s), for a total value of $42 billion.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And if for some reason you ran that company, a=
 good trade would be:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Have the coal division buy $100 milli=
on worth of graphics chips from the graphics-chip division.</li>=09<li styl=
e=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Use those chips to plan out your coal=C2=A0mining=
, or just chuck them in the ocean, doesn=E2=80=99t matter.</li>=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Let=E2=80=99s say it costs the graphics-chip divis=
ion $50 million to manufacture those chips.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=
=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inli=
ne-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">So this trade reduces your coal-m=
ining profit by $100 million<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-3=
" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-=
width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !import=
ant; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a>=C2=A0and increases your graphics-chip profit by $50 million.</li>=09<l=
i style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">This reduces the value of your coal-mining =
division by $600 million (at a 6x multiple)=C2=A0and increases the value of=
 your graphics-chip division by $1.8 billion (at a 36x multiple).</li>=09<l=
i style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You have increased the value of your compan=
y by $1.3 billion.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Free money! Note that this trade works even be=
tter if the coal division pays $200 million for the $100 million worth of c=
hips. There are infinite variations.=C2=A0Last month, the Wall Street Journ=
al <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34658364.258368=
/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9yZWFsLWVzdGF0ZS9zcGVjdGFjdWxhci1jcmFzaC1iZW5rby=
1zaWduYS1jNWRhZDI4NT9tb2Q9cmVhbC1lc3RhdGVfbGVhZF9zdG9yeQ/607f07ceef4b8524a3=
19a23cBb2e9b587" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_=
blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bo=
ttom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; =
background-color: #ccc;">published a story</a> about =E2=80=9CThe Spectacul=
ar Crash of a $30 Billion Property Empire,=E2=80=9D Signa Holding, a Europe=
an property and retail firm run by Ren=C3=A9=C2=A0Benko. One thing that con=
tributed to Signa=E2=80=99s rise and fall is that it was a property=C2=A0<e=
m>and=C2=A0</em>retail firm, two divisions with different valuations that d=
o deals with each other all the time. The Journal explains:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One key to Signa=E2=80=99s growing empire was =
a financial maneuver in which Benko=E2=80=99s companies functioned as both =
landlord and tenant for department stores. This allowed Signa to reap outsi=
ze benefits by moving money from its department store business to its landl=
ord business through hiked rents, former Signa employees involved said.=C2=
=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That extra rental income was worth far more in=
 the landlord arm through what a former employee called =E2=80=9Cmultiple a=
rbitrage.=E2=80=9D Long-term leases instantly increase the value of propert=
ies substantially=E2=80=94and investors tend to value income at landlords a=
t more than 20 times the annual proceeds. At retailers, where business is s=
een as more fickle, investors value it at less than half that level. This a=
llowed the real estate unit to borrow and raise investment based on the hig=
her valuations.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If one part of your business is valued at 20 t=
imes earnings, and another part of your business is valued at 10 times earn=
ings, and they do deals with each other, you want the higher-valued divisio=
n to get a better deal. If you save $1 in the 20x division=C2=A0and lose $1=
 in the 10x division, you have increased the overall value of your business=
 by $10.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t particularly know the market m=
ultiples for the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3=
4658364.258368/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzcwODQv=
MDAwMDAwNzA4NDIzMDAwMDEwL2FkbS0yMDIyMTIzMS5odG0jaTcyOGQ2OTg4M2U1YTRkYjRhY2R=
mYzk5YTU1MTAzMjVjXzEwNg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBda5eae07" itemprop=3D"Stor=
yLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" title=3D"page 92" style=3D=
"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px=
; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-colo=
r: #ccc;">various segments</a> of Archer-Daniels-Midland Co.=E2=80=99s busi=
ness. What I do know is that, for the last few years, ADM has been keen on =
growing its =E2=80=9CNutrition=E2=80=9D division, perhaps more so than its =
=E2=80=9CAg Services and Oilseeds=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9CCarbohydrate Soluti=
ons=E2=80=9D divisions. Nutrition makes flavors and other ingredients for h=
uman and animal food; ag services handles things like seed oils and peanuts=
; carbohydrate solutions mills corn and wheat. Just from the names, you get=
 the sense that a nutrition business might be more exciting than ADM=E2=80=
=99s traditional cyclical commodities businesses. Bloomberg News <a href=3D=
"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34658364.258368/aHR0cHM6Ly93=
d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDMtMTIvYWRtLXJlY29yZHMtY2h=
hcmdlLWFkanVzdHMtdGhyZWUteWVhcnMtb2YtaW50ZXJuYWwtc2FsZXM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDMxMj=
I0X01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX=
3Rlcm09MjQwMzEyJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB4a=
b77d61" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" st=
yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgroun=
d-color: #ccc;">reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">ADM has spent billions expanding i=
ts nutrition business since 2014, when it made its biggest-ever acquisition=
 =E2=80=94 the $3 billion buyout of European natural ingredient maker Wild =
Flavors =E2=80=94 in a bid to diversify from row crop grains and oilseeds i=
nto processed products. ADM also spent about $1.8 billion to buy an animal =
feed maker in 2019.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But the real way you know how important nutrit=
ion was to ADM is from how ADM=E2=80=99s executives were paid. Bloomberg Ne=
ws <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34658364.258368=
/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDEtMjQvYWRtLX=
BhcnRpYWxseS10aWVkLWVxdWl0eS1ib251c2VzLXRvLWdyb3d0aC1pbi11bml0LWF0LWNlbnRlc=
i1vZi1wcm9iZT9jbXBpZD1CQkQwMzEyMjRfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0=
bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDAzMTImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R=
1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBddf23d56" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D=
"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">reported in January</a>:</p=
>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">ADM=E2=80=99s board in 2020 and 2021 staked a =
considerable share of senior executives=E2=80=99 stock award payouts to the=
 profitability growth of its nutrition unit. The company blew past the goal=
s for the first round of awards, helping the executives collect shares wort=
h more than $70 million. Payouts for the second round of awards were set to=
 be determined early this year. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For awards like these, boards typically select=
 metrics that reflect the company=E2=80=99s broader financial goals, like a=
djusted earnings, return on invested capital or stock return relative to ri=
vals. ADM=E2=80=99s board for many years followed this principle.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But in 2020, it removed adjusted earnings befo=
re interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization as one of the key metrics=
 for executive stock awards and added something much more specific: growth =
of average operating profit in the nutrition segment. The three-year averag=
e had to exceed 10% for executives to receive their target payout. If the u=
nit=E2=80=99s growth hit 20%, they stood to receive twice as many shares.</=
p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CSome of these changes were designed t=
o emphasize our focus to significantly grow the nutrition segment of our bu=
siness,=E2=80=9D the company said in a filing at the time. In the most rece=
nt quarterly report, the unit made up about 8% of total company revenue.</p=
>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So $1 of profit at the relatively small nutrit=
ion segment was worth=C2=A0<em>much more</em>, to ADM=E2=80=99s top executi=
ves, than $1 of profit at the larger commodity segments. (Presumably the bo=
ard and executives also thought that $1 of income in nutrition was worth mo=
re=C2=A0<em>to shareholders</em>, to the market, to the company=E2=80=99s l=
ong-term valuation, than $1 of income at the other segments, but that=E2=80=
=99s not the essential point.)</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And it turns out that making food ingredients =
involves buying agricultural commodities. The rest of the story writes itse=
lf.=C2=A0The Wall Street Journal <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/34658364.258368/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9idXNpbmVzcy9lYXJu=
aW5ncy9hZG0tZGlzY2xvc2VzLWp1c3RpY2UtZGVwYXJ0bWVudC1wcm9iZS1pbnRvLWFjY291bnR=
pbmctNjQzMzZkMzc_bW9kPWhwX2xpc3RhX3BvczQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB79192f47"=
 itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color=
: #ccc;">reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">ADM said Tuesday that current and former emplo=
yees have received subpoenas from the Justice Department. In January ADM pl=
aced Chief Financial Officer Vikram Luthar on administrative leave after th=
e company said it was conducting an internal probe of accounting practices,=
 which ADM said followed a document request by the Securities and Exchange =
Commission. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On Tuesday, the Chicago-based company said its=
 accounting review found that some products sold internally between busines=
s divisions were priced at a discount compared with their market rate. =E2=
=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The company said its review covered the years =
2018 through 2023. In its annual filing with the SEC, the company lowered s=
ome past operating profits from its nutrition business by tens of millions =
of dollars while slightly raising profits in its other two main units. The =
company said the revisions didn=E2=80=99t impact overall earnings since the=
y were made between business segments.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yes, but overall earnings are not what ADM wan=
ted. It wanted higher and faster-growing nutrition earnings, because those =
earnings were worth more than ag services or carbohydrate earnings. If the =
carbohydrates division sells wheat to the nutrition division at market pric=
es, whatever. If it sells wheat to the nutrition division at a=C2=A0<em>dis=
count</em>, that juices nutrition earnings (good) at the cost of carbohydra=
tes earnings (who cares). If it just=C2=A0<em>gave=C2=A0the wheat away=C2=
=A0</em>to the nutrition division, that would be even better, but it would =
probably be too obvious and you=E2=80=99d get in trouble. But you shave a d=
ollar off the price here, a dollar there, and pretty soon you earn your bon=
us without anyone noticing. Or that=E2=80=99s the idea.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Obviously people noticed. Here=E2=80=99s the <=
a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34658364.258368/aHR=
0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9peHZpZXdlci9peC5odG1sP2RvYz0vQXJjaGl2ZXMvZWRnYXIvZG=
F0YS8wMDAwMDA3MDg0LzAwMDAwMDcwODQyNDAwMDAwOS9hZG0tMjAyMzEyMzEuaHRt/607f07ce=
ef4b8524a319a23cB6e253b6e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" t=
arget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Form 10-K</a> that ADM filed today:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">As previously disclosed, the Company received =
a voluntary document request from the SEC relating to intersegment sales be=
tween the Company=E2=80=99s Nutrition reporting segment and the Company=E2=
=80=99s Ag Services and Oilseeds and Carbohydrate Solutions reporting segme=
nts.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Company has historically disclosed in the =
footnotes to its financial statements that intersegment sales have been rec=
orded at amounts approximating market. In connection with the Investigation=
, the Company identified certain intersegment sales that occurred between t=
he Company=E2=80=99s Nutrition reporting segment and the Company=E2=80=99s =
Ag Services and Oilseeds and Carbohydrate Solutions reporting segments that=
 were not recorded at amounts approximating market.</p>
</blockquote>
