<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Pipelines</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The life of an investment banker is that you g=
o around pitching a bunch of companies to try to work on deals for them. An=
d some of those pitches eventually turn into assignments where you sign an =
engagement letter, do a deal for the company and get paid. So that=E2=80=99=
s the top (pitching) and the bottom (getting paid) of the funnel.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In between, there is ambiguity, and also most =
of the job. When you pitch a company=E2=80=99s chief financial officer on a=
 deal, it is unusual for her to reply =E2=80=9CI love it, where do I sign?=
=E2=80=9D It is pretty common for her to reply =E2=80=9Cno, but thanks for =
coming in,=E2=80=9D but it is also common for her to reply something like =
=E2=80=9Chmm this is interesting but could you do some more analysis on wha=
t the debt financing would look like?=E2=80=9D You don=E2=80=99t shove an e=
ngagement letter at her=C2=A0at that point. You go back and do the analysis=
. You send it to her. You call to follow up. You suggest some other analyse=
s that you could run. You offer to do all sorts of free work for her.=C2=A0=
You insinuate yourself into her work and her decision-making=C2=A0so that=
=C2=A0when she=C2=A0<em>does=C2=A0</em>want to do a deal, she naturally cho=
oses you to do it. A good investment banker will be doing a lot of unpaid w=
ork for a lot of potential clients, because that is the main way to generat=
e paid work from those clients.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Another part of the job, though, is updating y=
our bosses about what you are working on and how likely it is to lead to fe=
es. This is called a =E2=80=9Cpipeline report.=E2=80=9D Generally the subte=
xt here is that if you are working on a lot of promising stuff, that=E2=80=
=99s good for your near-term career prospects; if you are idle or working o=
nly on hopeless stuff, that=E2=80=99s bad. Certainly when I was an investme=
nt banker, my pipelines erred on the side of optimism. If I was occasionall=
y sending emails to a CFO saying =E2=80=9Chey can I do some free work for y=
ou,=E2=80=9D and she was not replying, well, that was a pretty promising le=
ad, for me. Good enough to put on the pipeline report, anyway. Call it a 25=
% chance of a $5 million fee?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Occasionally the incentives go the other way.=
=C2=A0Here is a <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34=
658364.258368/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtM=
DMtMTEvY2FudG9yLXN1ZXMtZXgtYmFua2Vycy1maXJtLWNsYWltaW5nLW1pbGxpb25zLWluLXN0=
b2xlbi1wcm9maXQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDMxMjI0X01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ=
1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjQwMzEyJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leX=
N0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB3470da13" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Bloomberg News story</a>=
 about how =E2=80=9CCantor Fitzgerald LP sued a firm launched by a group of=
 its former investment bankers, accusing them of stealing clients worth mil=
lions of dollars in profit.=E2=80=9D Here=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link=
.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34658364.258368/aHR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMuYndie=
C5pby9kb2N1bWVudHMvdXNlcnMvaXFqV0hCRmRmeElVL3JyZDlJWlBRRTZUZy92MA/607f07cee=
f4b8524a319a23cBa2a9f9e6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" ta=
rget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; =
border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style=
: solid; background-color: #ccc;">the lawsuit</a>, which claims that the ba=
nkers prepared for their departure by doing work for clients and=C2=A0<em>n=
ot=C2=A0</em>putting it in the pipeline:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">They worked on several deals for=C2=A0months u=
nder verbal agreements with Cantor clients, intentionally delaying the step=
s necessary to finalize a written agreement between the clients and Cantor.=
 The absence of executed contracts for these matters eased the PEI Bankers=
=E2=80=99 ability to convince the clients to terminate their relationship w=
ith Cantor and immediately transfer the matters to PEI after their departur=
e.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The PEI Bankers omitted multiple matters on wh=
ich they had verbal agreements with clients from their =E2=80=9Cpipeline=E2=
=80=9D=C2=A0reports of pending engagements that were regularly disclosed to=
 Cantor management, so as to hide the business opportunities that the PEI B=
ankers might take after they left.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This all makes sense but is incredibly alien t=
o my own experience in banking.=C2=A0<em>Not=C2=A0</em>putting=C2=A0<em>rea=
l=C2=A0</em>deals in the pipeline, just wild.</p>
