<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Bid/ask</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you are a private tech startup and your val=
uation has gone down, three things are probably true:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Your valuation has gone down in a som=
ewhat opaque way. It=E2=80=99s not like your stock traded on the stock exch=
ange at $100 a year ago and at $50 today; your stock doesn=E2=80=99t trade =
on the stock exchange. Maybe there are some secondary transactions that are=
 not quite representative, maybe <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/34658364.258368/aHR0cHM6Ly90ZWNoY3J1bmNoLmNvbS8yMDI0LzAxLzAy=
L2ZpZGVsaXR5LW1hcmtzLWRvd24teC10by1hbG1vc3QtYS10aGlyZC1vZi10aGUtaW52ZXN0bWV=
udC1wcmljZS8/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBfd9ef24d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" item=
scope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorat=
ion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00000=
0; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Fidelity marked dow=
n</a> its position, maybe you did a fundraising round at a 20% lower price =
but with some <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3465=
8364.258368/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjM=
tMDEtMDQvcHJpdmF0ZS1tYXJrZXRzLWRvbi10LWxpa2UtdG8tZ28tZG93bj9jbXBpZD1CQkQwMz=
EyMjRfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1d=
G1fdGVybT0yNDAzMTImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23c=
B0fffdc6c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank"=
 style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-w=
idth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgr=
ound-color: #ccc;">structure</a>=C2=A0that prevented the decline from being=
 steeper. The decline in value is a bit fuzzy.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-b=
ottom: 5px;">Even assuming that your latest market value is knowable,=C2=A0=
<em>you=C2=A0</em>probably think you=E2=80=99re worth more: You are an opti=
mistic tech founder, you are changing the world, this is a temporary blip, =
you will do an initial public offering in a year or two at 10 times today=
=E2=80=99s obviously wrong valuation.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5p=
x;">Assuming that your latest market value is knowable,=C2=A0<em>prospectiv=
e employees=C2=A0</em>probably think you=E2=80=99re worth less: Tech startu=
p employees want to get on a rocket ship; they want stock worth $100 now th=
at will be worth $1,000 at your IPO. Declining stock values are bad; they s=
uggest that there=E2=80=99s no rocket ship.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This makes it very hard to pay new employees i=
n stock:=C2=A0You=C2=A0will be miserable giving up stock at these low valua=
tions, while the employees won=E2=80=99t be all that excited about getting =
it. The bid/ask spread is too wide to strike a deal. The <a href=3D"https:/=
/link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34658364.258368/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQu=
Y29tL2NvbnRlbnQvY2MxMjU0NTctNWYyZC00NTdlLThmNmItMGJjM2Q2ODZkYWY1/607f07ceef=
4b8524a319a23cBe07237df" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" tar=
get=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; b=
order-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style:=
 solid; background-color: #ccc;">Financial Times reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Technology start-ups have slashed equity packa=
ges for new hires as they weather a prolonged downturn, according to new da=
ta from San Francisco-based software company Carta.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">People going to work at start-ups are receivin=
g 37 per cent less equity in their companies on average compared with 18 mo=
nths ago, the figures showed.=C2=A0Average salaries have barely changed dur=
ing that time, shrinking by 0.2 per cent since November 2022. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CCompanies are being very conservative=
 in how they think about managing both cash and equity in an uncertain mark=
et,=E2=80=9D said Tom Keiser, chief operating officer of Carta.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">He said start-ups were holding back shares to =
help raise more funds once market conditions improved, but added that worke=
rs had also contributed to the shift in compensation.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CAnother part of it is that employees =
no longer believe in trading hours or compensation for equity because they =
do not believe the market is there the way it was before to generate wealth=
,=E2=80=9D he said. =E2=80=9CHR departments are looking at what employees r=
eally value and they value cash more right now than they do equity.=E2=80=
=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When the stock is cheap, it is harder than eve=
r for startups to part with it, and easier than ever for employees to pass =
it up.</p>
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Factors</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you invest in stocks, your returns will com=
e from roughly three sources:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The broad stock market goes up or dow=
n.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You can get paid (or lose money=
) for taking on some particular systematic risk: Small companies=E2=80=99 s=
tocks tend=C2=A0to outperform large stocks, and cheap stocks (by price-to-b=
ook value) tend to outperform expensive ones.=C2=A0</li>=09<li style=3D"mar=
gin-bottom: 5px;">You can be idiosyncratically good at picking stocks.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The first thing is generally pretty easy to me=
asure; there are widely used broad market indexes. The second thing is less=
 obvious; someone needs to identify the systematic factors and measure the =
data. The third thing =E2=80=94=C2=A0alpha, investing skill =E2=80=94=C2=A0=
is=C2=A0generally what=E2=80=99s left over after the first two things.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This means that identifying and measuring fact=
ors =E2=80=94=C2=A0Thing 2 =E2=80=94 is very important. For one thing, thos=
e factors are part of a popular investment approach: There are funds that t=
ry to capture factor premia by, say, buying cheap stocks and avoiding expen=
sive ones, and you want to know how well that strategy works. For another t=
hing, lots of people=C2=A0<em>really=C2=A0</em>want to know how much invest=
ment skill their managers have =E2=80=94=C2=A0how much alpha they create =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0and since that is the residue after subtracting factor retur=
ns, you need to know what those are.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For many academic and other uses, the main fac=
tor model is the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3=
4658364.258368/aHR0cHM6Ly9jb3Jwb3JhdGVmaW5hbmNlaW5zdGl0dXRlLmNvbS9yZXNvdXJj=
ZXMvdmFsdWF0aW9uL2ZhbWEtZnJlbmNoLXRocmVlLWZhY3Rvci1tb2RlbC8/607f07ceef4b852=
4a319a23cB20046097" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">Fama-French three-factor model</a>, where the=
 three factors are market returns, size (=E2=80=9Csmall minus big=E2=80=9D)=
 and value (=E2=80=9Chigh minus low,=E2=80=9D that is, high book-to-price r=
atio minus low book-to-price ratio). And the main source of historical data=
 on the factors is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click=
/34658364.258368/aHR0cHM6Ly9tYmEudHVjay5kYXJ0bW91dGguZWR1L3BhZ2VzL2ZhY3VsdH=
kva2VuLmZyZW5jaC9kYXRhX2xpYnJhcnkuaHRtbA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBccd0c1d9"=
 itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color=
: #ccc;">Kenneth French=E2=80=99s website</a>. And here is a fun <a href=3D=
"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34658364.258368/aHR0cHM6Ly93=
d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2ZlYXR1cmVzLzIwMjQtMDMtMTEvYS1maWdodC1vdmVyLWZ=
hY3Rvci1pbnZlc3RpbmctdGVzdHMtYS1waWxsYXItb2YtbW9kZXJuLWZpbmFuY2U_Y21waWQ9Qk=
